<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Block the right countershaft assembly against the case wall. Slide the drive gear to the rear and engage
            with the sliding clutch splines. Use a hook around the 1st-2nd sliding clutch to tilt the front of the
            mainshaft up and lift the assembly from the case (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302975">Figure 75</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302975" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302975" filename="../figg13/G1302975.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 75. Tilt Front of Mainshaft Up</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>The drive gear is free and can fall from the shaft.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
